1258
01:10:23.791 --> 01:10:25.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[children giggling]

1259
01:10:31.250 --> 01:10:33.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[children exclaiming and laughing]

1260
01:10:36.250 --> 01:10:38.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not quite the same place,
is it? [chuckles]

1261
01:10:41.458 --> 01:10:42.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[straining]

1262
01:10:43.583 --> 01:10:44.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[panting]

1263
01:10:45.208 --> 01:10:46.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[knocking at door]

1264
01:10:49.250 --> 01:10:50.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[speaking Saami]

1265
01:10:50.500 --> 01:10:51.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Jesper] Hey.

1266
01:10:52.041 --> 01:10:53.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What're you doing here?

1267
01:10:53.416 --> 01:10:54.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[visitors speaking Saami]

1268
01:11:03.750 --> 01:11:05.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A true act of goodwill, huh?

1269
01:11:05.916 --> 01:11:07.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Always sparks another.

1270
01:11:08.208 --> 01:11:09.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Never fails.

1271
01:11:09.916 --> 01:11:12.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Remember, put the letter in the envelope.

1272
01:11:12.916 --> 01:11:15.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-And pass it down the line.
-Come on! It doesn't have to rhyme.

1273
01:11:15.250 --> 01:11:17.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Mrs. Krum] That's right, keep at it.
-Keep it short and sweet!

1274
01:11:17.500 --> 01:11:19.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No extra points for good spelling.

1275
01:11:19.250 --> 01:11:21.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Oh, you're doing so great, pumpkin.
-[Mrs. Krum] Let's go! One letter!

1276
01:11:21.833 --> 01:11:24.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Mr. Ellingboe] Come on,
it doesn't have to be Shakespeare, people.

1277
01:11:26.750 --> 01:11:27.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts]

1278
01:11:29.375 --> 01:11:30.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Whoa!

1279
01:11:30.750 --> 01:11:32.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Steady, ol' girl! Easy does it.

1280
01:11:35.791 --> 01:11:36.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, wow!

1281
01:11:40.250 --> 01:11:41.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct chatter]

1282
01:11:41.708 --> 01:11:45.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh-huh. Smooth lines. Good. Nice work.

1283
01:11:46.750 --> 01:11:47.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello!

1284
01:11:48.541 --> 01:11:49.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hi.

1285
01:11:52.458 --> 01:11:53.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

1286
01:11:53.875 --> 01:11:56.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What am I supposed to do, huh?

1287
01:11:57.083 --> 01:11:59.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Jesper] <i>Stay forever in this little town?</i>

1288
01:12:02.958 --> 01:12:04.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Hanging out with an old woodsman?</i>

1289
01:12:04.708 --> 01:12:06.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[upbeat music playing]

1290
01:12:07.708 --> 01:12:08.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing and cheering]

1291
01:12:10.791 --> 01:12:12.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Surrounded by crazy people?</i>

1292
01:12:14.666 --> 01:12:15.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Mrgu giggles]

1293
01:12:37.166 --> 01:12:38.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Never wanting anything more?</i>

1294
01:12:47.250 --> 01:12:51.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[indistinct chatter in Saami]
-[Mrgu giggling]

1295
01:12:53.666 --> 01:12:55.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Okay, are you gonna do that part or--

1296
01:12:55.666 --> 01:12:57.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How about you finish these and--

1297
01:12:57.291 --> 01:12:58.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[gasps]
-Whoa!

1298
01:13:00.125 --> 01:13:02.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[women speaking Saami]

1299
01:13:05.041 --> 01:13:09.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They insisted,
and I didn't want to be rude.

1300
01:13:09.250 --> 01:13:11.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't know... What do you...
Pfft. It's a lot of red.

1301
01:13:11.583 --> 01:13:12.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you... Is it too much?

1302
01:13:13.000 --> 01:13:14.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-No.
-[knocking at door]

1303
01:13:14.500 --> 01:13:17.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll just blindfold the reindeer
so they don't get dizzy.

1304
01:13:17.291 --> 01:13:18.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[chuckles] That's all. I'm kidding.
-Aw...

1305
01:13:18.541 --> 01:13:19.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm kidding. I'm kidding.

1306
01:13:19.583 --> 01:13:22.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It looks great. It looks good.
It's nice. It's...

1307
01:13:22.083 --> 01:13:23.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello, Jesper.

1308
01:13:23.375 --> 01:13:24.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dad? What?

1309
01:13:24.875 --> 01:13:27.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[clears throat] Sorry.
Let's, um... Let's talk outside.

1310
01:13:28.000 --> 01:13:29.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a little cramped in here.

1311
01:13:32.125 --> 01:13:33.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dad, what're you doing here?

1312
01:13:33.583 --> 01:13:35.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Time isn't up yet.
I've still got a few days until--

1313
01:13:35.833 --> 01:13:38.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[chuckles] Fourteen thousand letters
out of Smeerensburg?

1314
01:13:38.583 --> 01:13:40.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, I had to come and see it for myself.

1315
01:13:41.000 --> 01:13:42.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dad, you can't just show up and...

1316
01:13:42.791 --> 01:13:44.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait, what? 14,000?

1317
01:13:44.666 --> 01:13:47.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-That's not right. It--
-[Mrs. Krum] Oh, but it is.

1318
01:13:47.208 --> 01:13:49.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't be so modest.

1319
01:13:49.416 --> 01:13:50.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What're they doing here?

1320
01:13:50.541 --> 01:13:53.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They were the ones who alerted me
to what you've accomplished here.

1321
01:13:53.333 --> 01:13:56.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We couldn't let such a feat go unrewarded.

1322
01:13:56.625 --> 01:13:58.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Listen, whatever they told you--

1323
01:13:58.250 --> 01:14:00.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, then, ready to go?

1324
01:14:00.083 --> 01:14:01.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go? Where?

1325
01:14:01.541 --> 01:14:03.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles] Home, of course.

1326
01:14:03.875 --> 01:14:07.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A deal's a deal. The ordeal is over.

1327
01:14:08.125 --> 01:14:08.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Home?

1328
01:14:09.458 --> 01:14:12.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
With the personal butler
and the breakfast in bed and...

1329
01:14:13.166 --> 01:14:14.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
my silk sheets?

1330
01:14:14.333 --> 01:14:16.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No one deserves it more.

1331
01:14:16.625 --> 01:14:20.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wouldn't you agree, Mr. Klaus?

1332
01:14:22.916 --> 01:14:25.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, he was unbelievable!

1333
01:14:25.583 --> 01:14:29.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Encouraging children to write letters
and go to school!

1334
01:14:29.208 --> 01:14:32.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Mr. Ellingboe] Convincing the locals
to donate their labor to...

1335
01:14:32.375 --> 01:14:34.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
such a worthy cause.

1336
01:14:35.333 --> 01:14:36.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Johanssen] Indeed.

1337
01:14:37.041 --> 01:14:38.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, shall we then?

1338
01:14:40.541 --> 01:14:43.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps a minute to say your goodbyes,
of course.

1339
01:14:47.041 --> 01:14:48.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please, I can explain.

1340
01:14:48.916 --> 01:14:50.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I was--
-Oh, it's very clear.

1341
01:14:51.000 --> 01:14:52.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You just duped everyone

1342
01:14:52.333 --> 01:14:55.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so you could get back to your
puffed-up life back in the big town.

1343
01:14:55.708 --> 01:14:56.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Something like that?

1344
01:14:56.666 --> 01:15:01.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No! No. Well, at first maybe, yes,
but, Alva, please come...

1345
01:15:01.666 --> 01:15:02.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Alva, please come back.

1346
01:15:02.750 --> 01:15:06.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I, I didnt get the letters,
Id be cut off, but things changed!

1347
01:15:06.708 --> 01:15:08.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[speaking Saami]

1348
01:15:08.500 --> 01:15:09.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jesper!

1349
01:15:09.916 --> 01:15:12.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[sobbing] Jesper!
-Mrgu...

1350
01:15:14.583 --> 01:15:16.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Klaus, just listen. I--

1351
01:15:16.375 --> 01:15:18.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Everybody's out to get something, right?

1352
01:15:41.041 --> 01:15:42.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Johanssen] I thought...

1353
01:15:42.083 --> 01:15:44.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
well, a bit of hardship
might help straighten you out,

1354
01:15:44.791 --> 01:15:46.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but even I must admit that--

1355
01:15:46.791 --> 01:15:50.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, let's just say that there's
certainly a bright future

1356
01:15:50.416 --> 01:15:53.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
for the man who brought postal service
to Smeerensburg, that's for sure.

1357
01:15:53.833 --> 01:15:57.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And speaking of the future,
I look forward to discussing...

1358
01:16:01.541 --> 01:16:04.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One down, one to go.

1359
01:16:06.000 --> 01:16:10.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you ask me "who" right now, I swear!

1360
01:16:26.541 --> 01:16:29.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, now, finally leaving, aren't we?

1361
01:16:29.416 --> 01:16:31.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles] I... uh...

1362
01:16:32.166 --> 01:16:33.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anchors away, Captain.

1363
01:16:33.333 --> 01:16:35.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-We're sailing off at once.
-Well, that's a first.

1364
01:16:36.041 --> 01:16:36.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I beg your pardon?

1365
01:16:37.041 --> 01:16:39.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Never saw a postman
looking more miserable leaving

1366
01:16:39.750 --> 01:16:41.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
than on the day they came in.

1367
01:16:42.750 --> 01:16:45.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, well. Best leave it alone, I say.

1368
01:16:45.166 --> 01:16:47.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sure it's nothing that could fester

1369
01:16:47.333 --> 01:16:50.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and eventually become
a source of resentment and regret.

1370
01:17:21.083 --> 01:17:22.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Mrgu] Jesper!

1371
01:17:23.083 --> 01:17:24.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[panting]

1372
01:17:24.958 --> 01:17:26.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[speaking Saami]

1373
01:17:31.916 --> 01:17:33.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sobbing] Jesper.

1374
01:17:33.875 --> 01:17:35.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[speaking Saami]

1375
01:17:35.250 --> 01:17:36.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[crying]

1376
01:17:37.958 --> 01:17:39.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Cheer up, little one.

1377
01:17:41.625 --> 01:17:43.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think I may have missed my boat.

1378
01:17:44.125 --> 01:17:46.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps] Jesper!

1379
01:17:49.666 --> 01:17:51.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Jesper] So I told him.
I told him everything.

1380
01:17:52.166 --> 01:17:54.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And then he turned to me, and he said...

1381
01:17:54.750 --> 01:17:56.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[chuckles] ...he'd never been
more proud of me.

1382
01:17:57.208 --> 01:17:59.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And he hugged me. Can you believe that?

1383
01:17:59.916 --> 01:18:01.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought he'd be mad.

1384
01:18:01.208 --> 01:18:04.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[speaking Saami]

1385
01:18:04.083 --> 01:18:05.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, yeah, sure. I'll miss it.

1386
01:18:05.583 --> 01:18:09.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The big house, the having my every whim
tended to, the silk sheets.

1387
01:18:10.000 --> 01:18:12.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, God, the silk sheets!
Can we change the subject?

1388
01:18:12.833 --> 01:18:15.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[both laugh]

1389
01:18:15.208 --> 01:18:17.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anyways, anybody can get off a boat.

1390
01:18:17.750 --> 01:18:20.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The real trick is gonna be
convincing Klaus and Alva to give me an--

1391
01:18:21.583 --> 01:18:22.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? What's that?

1392
01:18:24.875 --> 01:18:25.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's the clans!

1393
01:18:27.833 --> 01:18:28.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Klaus!

1394
01:18:32.458 --> 01:18:34.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man speaking Saami]

1395
01:18:37.875 --> 01:18:38.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Klaus] Slowly.

1396
01:18:39.458 --> 01:18:41.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Slowly. Slowly.

1397
01:18:41.875 --> 01:18:42.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A little bit...

1398
01:18:48.291 --> 01:18:49.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Mrs. Krum] Well, well.

1399
01:18:50.125 --> 01:18:51.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Isn't this convenient?

1400
01:18:51.958 --> 01:18:53.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps and speaks Saami]

1401
01:18:54.041 --> 01:18:55.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What're you doing here?

1402
01:18:55.375 --> 01:18:57.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why, we were just thinking,

1403
01:18:57.583 --> 01:19:01.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"Don't our children
also deserve a present?"

1404
01:19:01.333 --> 01:19:02.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And lookie here!

1405
01:19:02.666 --> 01:19:05.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've already got her favorite thing
in the world.

1406
01:19:05.125 --> 01:19:07.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A nice, big piata!

1407
01:19:07.458 --> 01:19:09.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[all gasp]
-Hey, you put... [grunts]

1408
01:19:09.708 --> 01:19:11.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
...one hand on those toys and I swear I--

1409
01:19:11.833 --> 01:19:13.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stand back. All right.

1410
01:19:13.333 --> 01:19:15.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do what you will with the toys.

1411
01:19:15.416 --> 01:19:16.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But no one gets hurt.

1412
01:19:16.958 --> 01:19:19.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Suits us just fine.

1413
01:19:19.291 --> 01:19:20.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Magdalone and Olaf grumble]

1414
01:19:20.500 --> 01:19:23.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How long until children
go back to the old ways

1415
01:19:24.041 --> 01:19:26.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
once there are no toys to bribe them with?

1416
01:19:27.416 --> 01:19:29.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How long until they
turn against each other?

1417
01:19:30.791 --> 01:19:35.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And how long until the grown-ups follow?

1418
01:19:36.666 --> 01:19:37.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

1419
01:19:37.833 --> 01:19:39.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[screams]
-[Jesper screaming]

1420
01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:47.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jesper?

1421
01:19:47.208 --> 01:19:48.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The postman!

1422
01:19:52.708 --> 01:19:54.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ha! Eat our snow, you...

1423
01:19:54.916 --> 01:19:56.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're not attached.
Why aren't they attached?

1424
01:19:56.958 --> 01:19:57.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought they were attached.

1425
01:19:58.041 --> 01:20:01.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I would never, in a million years,
have done what I just did

1426
01:20:01.166 --> 01:20:02.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
if I didn't think these were attached.

1427
01:20:02.625 --> 01:20:03.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
After them!

1428
01:20:03.750 --> 01:20:07.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who leaves a sleigh
unattached like... Aah!

1429
01:20:07.333 --> 01:20:08.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Destroy those toys!

1430
01:20:08.625 --> 01:20:10.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Stop them at any cost!
-Mine!

1431
01:20:10.958 --> 01:20:13.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mine! Mine!

1432
01:20:14.083 --> 01:20:15.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Mine!
-[Olaf chuckling]

1433
01:20:17.833 --> 01:20:19.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Magdalone in raspy voice] Mine...

1434
01:20:20.666 --> 01:20:23.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mine!

1435
01:20:30.208 --> 01:20:32.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I could really use a hand here.

1436
01:20:32.625 --> 01:20:35.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Use." Interesting choice of word.

1437
01:20:35.291 --> 01:20:37.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Really? You're gonna
go for the guilt trip now?

1438
01:20:37.791 --> 01:20:39.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Smash those toys to pieces!

1439
01:20:45.958 --> 01:20:47.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The toys!

1440
01:20:47.333 --> 01:20:49.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-We have to close that bag!
-What do you care?

1441
01:20:49.750 --> 01:20:52.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I thought you were leaving.
-Great. Sure. I'll tell you what.

1442
01:20:52.875 --> 01:20:55.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let's continue discussing
what a horrible person I am

1443
01:20:55.916 --> 01:20:59.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
while I most likely break my neck
trying to save the children's toys,

1444
01:20:59.375 --> 01:21:01.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-why don't we?
-Get down there!

1445
01:21:01.541 --> 01:21:03.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Stop those toys!
-[screaming]

1446
01:21:04.125 --> 01:21:04.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

1447
01:21:05.041 --> 01:21:06.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh... Klaus?

1448
01:21:07.541 --> 01:21:08.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm.

1449
01:21:12.458 --> 01:21:13.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[all scream]

1450
01:21:17.041 --> 01:21:20.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nice move! How'd you know
I wouldn't get knocked off too?

1451
01:21:20.125 --> 01:21:21.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Never mind. Don't answer that.

1452
01:21:21.916 --> 01:21:22.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[screams]

1453
01:21:23.583 --> 01:21:24.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Mine!
-[Jesper] Whoa!

1454
01:21:25.041 --> 01:21:27.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Go! Go! We're dead!
We're dead! We're dead!

1455
01:21:27.291 --> 01:21:28.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mine!

1456
01:21:29.125 --> 01:21:31.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[growls] Mine!
-[exclaims]

1457
01:21:32.791 --> 01:21:33.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts]

1458
01:21:33.833 --> 01:21:35.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Mr. Ellingboe] Pumpkin!

1459
01:21:35.291 --> 01:21:37.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm still proud of you, you hear me?

1460
01:21:38.166 --> 01:21:39.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[ice cracking]

1461
01:21:40.625 --> 01:21:42.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[exclaims]

1462
01:21:44.291 --> 01:21:45.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mine?

1463
01:21:54.083 --> 01:21:55.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're losing toys!

1464
01:21:56.333 --> 01:21:57.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts]

1465
01:21:57.250 --> 01:21:58.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

1466
01:22:00.583 --> 01:22:01.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[both screaming]

1467
01:22:03.333 --> 01:22:04.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts]

1468
01:22:05.041 --> 01:22:07.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[all screaming]
-[Mrs. Krum] Oh, no!

1469
01:22:07.125 --> 01:22:08.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Stop! Stop!
-[Mr. Ellingboe] Oh, my goodness!

1470
01:22:08.583 --> 01:22:11.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Oh, no, no, no! No!
-[groans]

1471
01:22:13.083 --> 01:22:14.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Jesper screaming]

1472
01:22:16.250 --> 01:22:17.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunting]

1473
01:22:20.708 --> 01:22:21.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

1474
01:22:22.791 --> 01:22:23.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunting]

1475
01:22:25.375 --> 01:22:27.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jesper! Let go!

1476
01:22:27.416 --> 01:22:30.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-It's not worth it!
-Are you crazy? No!

1477
01:22:35.916 --> 01:22:36.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[panting heavily]

1478
01:22:38.666 --> 01:22:39.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[panting]

1479
01:22:40.625 --> 01:22:43.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
See? Nothing to it. Just...

1480
01:22:43.125 --> 01:22:45.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Mrs. Krum] I wouldn't be so sure.

1481
01:22:47.458 --> 01:22:48.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait! No, no, no!

1482
01:22:49.458 --> 01:22:54.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No! No, no, no! No!

1483
01:23:00.916 --> 01:23:05.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This town was built
on resentment and spite.

1484
01:23:05.166 --> 01:23:08.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And it'll stay that way
as long as a Krum...

1485
01:23:08.166 --> 01:23:09.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or an Ellingboe!

1486
01:23:09.458 --> 01:23:10.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ugh.

1487
01:23:10.375 --> 01:23:12.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
...have something to say about it.

1488
01:23:13.250 --> 01:23:16.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's go. We're done here.

1489
01:23:16.083 --> 01:23:18.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Mr. Ellingboe] Well said.
Wait, does that mean the feud is back on?

1490
01:23:18.916 --> 01:23:20.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No more truce?

1491
01:23:20.250 --> 01:23:21.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Mrs. Krum] First thing tomorrow.

1492
01:23:22.791 --> 01:23:24.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
